[
  {
    "text": "The Pupil asks: 'At whose wish does the mind sent forth proceed on its errand? At whose command does the first breath go forth? At whose wish do we utter this speech? What god directs the eye, or the ear?",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 1,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "b56c5f65c92652cb"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Teacher replies: 'It is the ear of the ear, the mind of the mind, the speech of speech, the breath of breath, and the eye of the eye. When freed from the senses the wise, on departing from this world, become immortal.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 2,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "death",
      "liberation"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "401cb3f5dfcd473c"
  },
  {
    "text": "'The eye does not go thither, nor speech, nor mind. We do not know, we do not understand, how any one can teach it.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 3,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "0ca07634fb69b453"
  },
  {
    "text": "'It is different from the known, it is also above the unknown, thus we have heard from those of old, who taught us this.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 4,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "40fcd606129de949"
  },
  {
    "text": "'That which is not expressed by speech and by which speech is expressed, that alone know as Brahman, not that which people here adore.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 1,
    "verse": 5,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
