  },
  {
    "text": "The Teacher says: 'If thou thinkest I know it well, then thou knowest surely but little, what is that form of Brahman known, it may be, to thee?",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 1,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman",
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "3ac0957701304193"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Pupil says: 'I do not think I know it well, nor do I know that I do not know it. He among us who knows this, he knows it, nor does he know that he does not know it.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 2,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "593b9ae11ff4015c"
  },
  {
    "text": "'He by whom it is not thought, by him it is thought; he by whom it is thought, knows it not. It is not understood by those who understand it, it is understood by those who do not understand it.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 3,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "0e2bbc882e202ce4"
  },
  {
    "text": "'It is thought to be known as if by awakening, and then we obtain immortality indeed. By the Self we obtain strength, by knowledge we obtain immortality.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 4,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "atman",
      "death",
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "252d74ffecee0060"
  },
  {
    "text": "'If a man know this here, that is the true end of life; if he does not know this here, then there is great destruction. The wise who have thought on all things and recognised the Self in them become immortal, when they have departed from this world.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 2,
    "verse": 5,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "atman",
      "death",
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "e869ddeef6c806bb"
  },
  {
    "text": "Brahman obtained the victory for the Devas. The Devas became elated by the victory of Brahman, and they thought, this victory is ours only, this greatness is ours only.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "1c1e31414ca50f6f"
  },
  {
    "text": "Brahman perceived this and appeared to them. But they did not know it, and said: 'What sprite is this?",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman",
      "knowledge"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "b1f0e739c137784d"
  },
  {
    "text": "They said to Agni: 'O Gatavedas, find out what sprite this is.' 'Yes,' he said.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "a0007027c112fa78"
  },
  {
    "text": "He ran toward it, and Brahman said to him: 'Who are you?' He replied: 'I am Agni, I am Gatavedas.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "9169783e2d63eaa1"
  },
  {
    "text": "Brahman said: 'What power is in you?' Agni replied: 'I could burn all whatever there is on earth.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "f6f1fe977314dd20"
  },
  {
    "text": "Brahman put a straw before him, saying: 'Burn this.' He went towards it with all his might, but he could not burn it. Then he returned thence and said: 'I could not find out what sprite this is.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "810a832cf191bf0e"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then they said to Vayu: 'O Vayu, find out what sprite this is.' 'Yes,' he said.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "b2dc03b3a1015a56"
  },
  {
    "text": "He ran toward it, and Brahman said to him: 'Who are you?' He replied: 'I am Vayu, I am Matarisvan.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "96a61e35125eb659"
  },
  {
    "text": "Brahman said: 'What power is in you?' Vayu replied: 'I could take up all whatever there is on earth.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "309999559391bc70"
  },
  {
    "text": "Brahman put a straw before him, saying: 'Take it up.' He went towards it with all his might, but he could not take it up. Then he returned thence and said: 'I could not find out what sprite this is.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "fb9951ba72989423"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then they said to Indra: 'O Maghavan, find out what sprite this is.' He went towards it, but it disappeared from before him.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "7c557d56d2908881"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then in the same space he came towards a woman, highly adorned: it was Uma, the daughter of Himavat. He said to her: 'Who is that sprite?",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "62b7eafa35dc6a67"
  },
  {
    "text": "She replied: 'It is Brahman. It is through the victory of Brahman that you have thus become great.' After that he knew that it was Brahman.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 1,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "bab99a9f1968b1e4"
  },
  {
    "text": "Therefore these Devas, viz. Agni, Vayu, and Indra, are, as it were, above the other gods, for they touched it nearest.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 2,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "49026c773a0b15da"
  },
  {
    "text": "And therefore Indra is, as it were, above the other gods, for he touched it nearest, he first knew it.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 3,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "c9a28694474f9320"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is the teaching of Brahman, with regard to the gods: It is that which now flashes forth in the lightning, and now vanishes again.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 4,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "2cfa465825af2894"
  },
  {
    "text": "And this is the teaching of Brahman, with regard to the body: It is that which seems to move as mind, and by it imagination remembers again and again.",
    "scripture": "Kena Upanishad",
    "tradition": "hindu_vedanta",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 5,
    "translator": "Max Müller",
    "year": 1879,
    "language": "en",
    "license_tier": "A",
    "source_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/hin/sbe01/index.htm",
    "themes": [
      "brahman"
    ],
    "sanskrit": null,
    "speaker": null,
    "chapter_name": null,
    "commentary_source": null,
    "chunk_type": "verse",
    "verse_type": "verse",
    "chunk_id": "ac0eddee1418c5ff"
